{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> τάφος</b> [ᾰ], ὁ, <br /> (θάπτω) <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1> <b>funeral-rites</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.619, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.547 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; δαινύναι τάφον to give a <b>funeral-feast</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.29, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.309 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τελέσαι τάφον Ἕκτορι δίῳ to perform <b>the funeral-rites</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.660 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; so ὃν πόλις στυγεῖ, σὺ τιμήσεις τάφ; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 1051; τάφῳ κτερίζειν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 203; τάφον τινὸς θέσθαι [prev. author] “OT” 1447; τ. περιστέλλειν νεκροῦ [prev. author] “Aj.” 1170 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τάφου τυχεῖν obtain <b>the rites of burial</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 47; τοιόσδε ὁ τ. ἐγένετο 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.47 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i> of a single funeral, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 414a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so of cremation, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Clitarchus Gnomologus 32 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.2</b></Level3> <b>the act of performing the funeral-rites</b>, τοῦδε τοῦ τ. φήσεις μετασχεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 534. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.II</b></Level2> <b>grave, tomb</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 477, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 8(7).63, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 686, “Ch.” 168, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1218f, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.136, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.26, etc. (never in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i> of a single grave, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 411 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὄντες ἐν τάφοις <b>dead and buried</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 767 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; μέγας γ᾽ ὀφθαλμὸς οἱ πατρὸς τάφοι <b>his being dead and buried</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 987:— γῦπες ἔμψυχοι τάφοι 5th c.BC: Gorgias Rhetor et Sophista 5a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.II.2</b></Level3> ἔμψυχός τις τ. a 'living skeleton', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DMort.” 6.2. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.II.3</b></Level3> ={βωμός}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Duris Epigrammaticus 34 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.II.4</b></Level3> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD: Cypria for φόνος, Scholia 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.29. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5028","accentedUnicode":"τάφος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2290","matchingForm":"θάπτω","stepTransliteration":"thaptō","gloss":"to bury","_zh_tw_Gloss":"埋葬","_es_Gloss":"enterrar","_zh_Gloss":"埋葬"}],"shortDef":"tomb, grave","mediumDef":"tomb, grave <br /><b>a sepulchre, grave, tomb,</b> <ref='Mat.23.27, 29; 27:61, 64, 66; 28:1'>Mt. 23:27, 29; 27:61, 64, 66; 28:1</ref>; <i>metaphorically</i> <ref='Rom.3.13'>Rom. 3:13</ref>*","stepGloss":"grave","stepTransliteration":"tafos","count":7,"_es_Definition":"sepultura, tumba","_zh_tw_Definition":"墳墓, 墓穴","_zh_Definition":"坟墓, 墓穴","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"mồ chôn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"墳墓","_es_Gloss":"tumba","_zh_Gloss":"坟墓"}]}